runs.comm: Kyle Mills starts with a dot, which will please him, even though it was a thigh-high full toss
steered to the off-side for another dot, found the fielder
a quick single and they're away at last, Gilchrist poking forward and setting off for an easy one
Clarke's strike-rate leaps to 400 hundred per cent with a drive through the covers for four
huge appeal from bowler and keeper as Pu..Clarke pads up to one which nips back in from just outside off but would have gone over
swing away, hit powerfully to mid-off
good delivery across the left hander, who drives to mid-off
stunning catch! Worth the entry fee alone, Patel leaping up and up to pluck a stunner at backward point from a firm Gilchrist drive, the batsman looking to take advantage of a wide one
lets that one go through on the rise
another leave, that one right on the dollar
a drive to short cover this time
a drive back to the bowler
pushed forward for a quick single
pushed to deep midwicket, with Patel falling over and laughing as he throws and trips over his own feet
a single to third man this time
pushed to square for a comfortable two
up there, driven to mid-off, and there's a big shout of "No"
straight to the batsman, who defended on the back foot
driven to mid-on, and they eschew a risky single
hostile bouncer, straight and Clarke pulls out of the hook
dragged it a touch wide and short, inviting the straight drive over long-off, an aggressive six
forceful drive over cover, the ball bouncing about two metres short of the rope and running on
"Yeah, yeah" is the cry as there's a dink and run into the off-side
down the track and over cover to help hurry Australia's total along
outside off, Clarke smashes it straighter, so straight it cannons into the sticks at the other end
outside off again, but wider, and curling even more so, Clarke swishes gamely but it's called wide
beautiful straight drive back past the bowler
a steer to square leg
down the ground, Hussey delights his home fans with a one-step, one-bounce four of a straight drive up and over
over the top again and that's a well-struck lofted drive once more
doesn't quite get hold of the pull off the front foot from outside off, the eager Patel racing from square to return with a whip
left alone outside off
a quick single this time
dropped... if you want to be strict - that was battered back to him and he palms it down just above his knee, crashing to the floor in the process
a swipe wide of mid-on races away
good response, Oram seeing Hussey was moving backwards so he followed him with a short one which was steered into the on-side for a comfortable single
drags it short, Clarke advances and drives strongly to mid-on to steal the strike
pushed into the leg-side for a quick, but well run, two to bring up Australia's fifty
good yorker, Clarke with a desperate late jab down of the bat
a touch shorter this time, Clarke nimble again driving out to long-off
stumped! Really sharp stuff from Patel, with the flight, and McCullum, with a nifty stumping - Hussey advancing down the track keen for more runs
off the mark straight away with a cut in front of point
single to square leg, the call of "Yes, mate" appearing to reflect the jovial nature of this match
played out to point
pushed forward
defended forward
swiped into the leg-side
a leg bye, as it says on the tin
cut to short third man up inside the circle for a single
driven out straight to long-on
a forearm jab wide of long-on, and there's no hope for Lou Vincent
pushed up there, driven into his foot
opens his stance to drive out to short midwicket
a touch of out-curve as that pitches on leg and is driven back out to long-on, great drive and return from Vincent just inside the rope
a strong drive, though not quite timed, out to long-off
beaten, went through to the keeper
tucked down to fine leg
great fielding out at very long-on, a cross-batted lofted drive, Taylor running round to keep it in, pusing it towards Sinclair.. Taylor ran round him to return it
he's not smiling now as he holes out at deep long-on
a single out to mid-on, Symonds took it as he wsa on strike
off the mark straight away with a push down and run into midwicket
beaten there, outside off
beaten again, that one just too quick for Voges I'm afraid
Voges comes down the track, a nice bit of aggression, but ducks at the last second
good strike that one, a cross-bat heave in front of midwicket, taken from outside off
strayed down off and Voges doesn't miss out in timing it behind square but not quite the placement
outside off, Voges waits and plays easily off the back foot, a neat steer backward of point
bit of a false offering from Symonds
Steered behind square
Voges nearly pops back to the bowler
they decide not to risk the single to the on-side
pulled to square
driven forward and the single is roundly applauded by a packed WACA audience
majestic shot, Symonds edges back to give himself room to drive up and over extra cover, such a clean strike right through the ball
much less convincing, but nevertheless a four, a Chinese cut, Symonds looking to drive to cover instead gets the inside edge through fine leg
worked out to long-on this time
short and pulled round in front of square, didn't quite time that but the crowd don't care as they've got something else to cheer - the hundred's up
strayed down leg, Symonds tracks it off his toes through fine leg, the nearest fielder was ten metres away as that ran on
outside off, Symonds opens the face and runs it down to third man where it's gathered easily
that's a big six, wide of long-on, just lifted there easily by Symond's muscles
pushed down for a quick single this time
a swing of a pull behind square
pushed straight to a fielder this time
turned in front of midwicket, good placement there
down leg, a simple Symonds offering this time, merely presenting the face of the bat to turn it down behind square and it fair races
gets away with a low full toss, driven to mid-on
looks to work to leg but doesn't quite time it
down the track and driven out towards mid-on, he didn't quite strike that one cleanly
on off, well bowled, but Symonds bisects the longs off and on (if that's the correct way to pluralise them), my, that was yet another clean strike
brings up his fifty with the best shot of the match so far, a huge strike wide of long-on
nice response, fuller delivery and Symonds checks his shot at the last minute, turning it into a short jab of an on-drive out towards mid-on, and he keeps the strike
well bowled, pushing him back deep into his crease to work a rising delivery into the on-side
dragged it short, worked to midwicket for an easy two
quicker delivery, good thinking, Symonds works it down towards third man
down the track, Voges had to readjust as the ball came slower than he was expecting, but manages to drive it wide of long-on
good length again, Voges steps back to make room to drive into the covers, but doesn't have much power
on leg, bounces up and Symonds pats it back down to fine leg to take the strike again, which is a good move
leg-side full toss, you can't bowl there to him etc, and that's pulled off the bottom of his bat for yet another colossal six
good recovery, Patel up there on off, but Symonds cuts out to point
pulled in front of midwicket
dragged it down and Voges holes out at deep midwicket for a helpful 26
worked to the covers
off the mark with a push off the hips to midwicket
a dink down and run, tip-and-run beach cricket kind of fare
tucked away nicely off the hips for an easy two
full delivery, not too much wrong with it, but Symonds turns it into a half-volley and hammers it away through cover
round the wicket now, well bowled, up there outside off and Symonds backs away, then cuts back out and runs back well to get in for the second and keep the strike
plugs a single to long-off, can't quite get the return this time
outside off and that's what Pomersbach is made of - his full-blooded pull in front of midwicket flying flat and true and delighting the crowd

cracking catch from Taylor, sliding just inside the rope. There's a referral, but ... oh hang on, it's been given not out as he was deemed to have spilled it at the last minute, although he looked to have full control for several seconds
worked to midwicket, just about on the circle
driven out to mid-off for a quick single
very well bowled, tidy yorker, Pomersbach nudges it and answers Symonds' call for the single
wide full toss, possibly deliberate, Symonds gets the single out to deep cover
didn't quite mean to play through third man, but the thick outside edge races away
worked out to deep midwicket, more electric fielding from Taylor
pushed to cover
the slower ball, rolled out of the back of the hand, only just clears deep midwicket, and they get back for two
aerial drive to mid-off and Pomersbach is furious with himself at getting out with three balls to go
pushed up there, Symonds works it out to cover and Noffke is out without facing a ball thanks to the return and Gillespie's work
no-ball, the last thing they need, Symonds drives out to the covers
...but Lee can't, that was a decent delivery, a straight bouncer, Lee wafts at it off the back foot but doesn't connect
